validate

public boolean validate(Map<String,File> typeToFiles)
Description copied from interface: BatchInputFileSetType
Runs validation upon uploaded files. Note the files passed in the Map may be located in a temporary directory rather than the directory returned by BatchInputFileSetType.getDirectoryPath(String) If validation fails, the implementation is responsible for adding error messages to the KFSConstants#GLOBAL_ERRORS property string in the ErrorMap If validation requires opening up input streams/readers/etc. on the files, implementations of this method must close all input streams/readers on files contained within the map. Failure to do so may cause the files to be undeletable.

Specified by:
validate in interface BatchInputFileSetType
Parameters:
typeToFiles - a map consisting of file type Strings (see BatchInputFileSetType.getFileTypes()) to file mappings
Returns:
true if validation succeeds, false otherwise
See Also:
BatchInputFileSetType.validate(java.util.Map)
